# Ship every change to GitHub

The developer does **not** run this plugin locally. They update/install hermes-chat from the **Hermes GUI** against the GitHub repo. Unpushed work is invisible to them.

## After every add or fix

Before ending the turn (unless they explicitly say not to):

1. **Build** anything that needs a build (see below).
2. **Commit** source **and** built artifacts.
3. **Push** to `origin` on the current branch.

Do not wait to be asked “did you build/commit/push?” — that is part of finishing the change.

## What to build

Hermes plugin install does **not** run a frontend build. Committed `dist` must be production-ready:

| Area | Build | Commit these outputs |
|---|---|---|
| Chat UI | `npm run build` in `webui/` | `webui/dist/**` |
| Dashboard tab | hand-written; no separate build | `dashboard/dist/index.js` (edit and commit as-is) |

If you change TypeScript/React under `webui/src/`, rebuild before commit. Stale `webui/dist` means the installed plugin still serves the old UI.

## Exceptions

- Skip commit/push only when the user says so, or when the change is purely local scratch they asked not to publish.
- Still never force-push `main`/`master` or skip hooks unless they explicitly request it.
